{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"83544de54ad3c020de1caa4b757708deb8ccaa079205d05b8c2e5959f9c17886","slug":"book.data-acquisition-and-preparation","location":"/book/08_data_acquisition_and_preparation.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Data Acquisition & Preparation","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Florian Huber","given":"Florian","family":"Huber"},"name":"Florian Huber","id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course","copyright":"2025","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/blob/main/book/08_data_acquisition_and_preparation.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/edit/main/book/08_data_acquisition_and_preparation.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"08_data_acquisition_and_preparation.md","url":"/build/08_data_acquisition_-048d60f8fd77d282ab025d8e95e39e15.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The foundational pillar of any data science project lies in the data itself. Sounds obvious, yet in practice, many aspiring data scientists will still be surprised by ","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"Xt7ueZGzmh"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"how much the quality and quantity of data matters for the success of a data science project","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"gP9dNr5Iqd"}],"key":"N3x0p2fjjM"},{"type":"text","value":". Without pertinent and high-quality data, even the most sophisticated algorithms will fall short of producing meaningful results. This chapter aims at building a first intuition about the process of data acquisition and preparation, elucidating best practices to ensure your data science journey is built on solid ground. I am fairly certain that many of the parts of the data science pipeline that we will see in the following chapters will appear much fancier and more exciting. But ultimately, it is often times the data acquisition, preparation, and processing part that makes the largest impact.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"r7fohZnztv"}],"key":"RPODSV9iot"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Data Acquisition","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"LllsawaSsr"}],"identifier":"data-acquisition","label":"Data Acquisition","html_id":"data-acquisition","implicit":true,"key":"CLHpCwgpcY"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Before plunging into data collection, it’s imperative to ask: What’s the problem at hand? What questions to we want to answer? And, what kind of data do we need for this?","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"mW0ju9g3nE"}],"key":"jaTVOEvJ4u"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Key Considerations:","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"DYD2m5QJmh"}],"identifier":"key-considerations","label":"Key Considerations:","html_id":"key-considerations","implicit":true,"key":"BLOEVkisW9"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Type of Data Needed","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"dPclbx9ske"}],"key":"bYDLdZxMwP"},{"type":"text","value":": What kind of information will help address the problem? Is it quantitative, qualitative, temporal, or spatial?","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"POVVHpnaWW"}],"key":"Xxqyd8RJ6u"}],"key":"uEMIX4LiZG"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Data Quality and Quantity","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"W521yVxj7x"}],"key":"TA4mreTZA0"},{"type":"text","value":": Do the data offer enough breadth and depth to draw meaningful conclusions? Are there gaps or inconsistencies that might pose challenges?","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"fzJuRYRfrt"}],"key":"E2jvIMThoM"}],"key":"jghAgKXmXT"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Data Sources","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"RxgWlBLWJV"}],"key":"vQPOU24QhF"},{"type":"text","value":": Is the data readily available? Is it accessible? And can we trust the source?","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"BGyVSPrCbD"}],"key":"oo0JtkIOTs"}],"key":"Rzb8NrhFmp"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type